Package ralgorithm

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Movement
    Movement is a logical step of operations performable on a robot.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Algorithm
    Abstract class for algorithms involving reconfiguration of Robot Objects.
    Combing
    Transforms a Source Robot, S, into a Target Robot, T, in O(n) parallel steps
    CombToLine
    Algorithm to tranform a Combed robot into a line of modules.
    ConnectAll
    Connects all modules that have some connectivity to the graph to any possible neighbor
    ContractAll
    Implementation of a movement which contracts all the arms in the robot
    CornerOneTunnel
    The OneTunnel is the most primitive kTunnel from Start to End in one turn.
    Elevator  
    ExpandAll
    Movmenet implementation to expand all of the arms in a robot.
    ExpandedOneTunnel
    The OneTunnel is the most primitive kTunnel from Start to End in one turn.
    FlipConfiguration
    Movment implementation that expands robot if contracted, or contracts if expanded.
    MakeTunnel
    Movement that creates a disconnected tunnel from the robot.
    Melt
    Implementation of the Melt algorithm to melt a robot in some direction
    OneTunnel
    The OneTunnel is the most primitive kTunnel from Start to End in one turn.
    ParallelMove
    Class that represents a Parallel Move, or a series of steps to be run concurrently
    Slide
    The Slide is a movement sliding one module along two adjacent modules.
    Staircase
    Implementation of a Staircase movement that tranforms a a rectangle of k1 by k2 modules in to one of k2 by k1 modules
    Wall
    Wall class that represents a level of Modules in a robot
